=20

One of the fundamental issues is you get to the top of the hierarchy at =
FENZ by being a great firefighter, or at least a popular one, and that =
doesn=E2=80=99t equate with the type of leadership and vision necessary =
for the role.  I=E2=80=99d argue it may well mitigate against it because =
firefighters are typically quite structured and mechanical in their =
thinking, rather than innovative and exploratory.  So they struggle to =
make progress or have it stick.

=20

You=E2=80=99ll see a code of behavior on the webpage.  That=E2=80=99s =
great but they=E2=80=99ll almost certainly fail at promulgating and =
implementing it. =20

=20

It=E2=80=99s where your Indigometrics sounded interesting to me.

=20

Other challenges include:

=20

We=E2=80=99ve recently integrated all forest fire fighting and =
metropolitan firefighting into a single organization.  But the two =
groups have vastly different cultures that need to be made one.

=20

And as I mentioned, we=E2=80=99re made up of around 880 disparate and =
far-flung fire-stations.  Each one its own little satrapy with very =
little oversight or influence from the regional HQ.  So where =
we=E2=80=99d like organizational culture to approach uniformity=E2=80=A6 =
instead we have a different culture behind every blade of grass.

